resultMetric.name: Computational Latency
resultMetric.description: Computational Latency is defined by the time expended from acquiring the device data to receiving a trust score from a remote server (e.g., cloud) and is computed as 2Tc + Tp, where Tc and Tp denote the communication latency from device to remote server and vice versa and the processing latency
